---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';

const WORKSHOP_TITLE = 'Practical Generative AI Workshops for Teams | Auston Horras';
const WORKSHOP_DESCRIPTION =
	'Practical generative AI workshops for teams and leaders. Learn how to work with AI effectively using clear workflows, constraints, and real-world examples.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={WORKSHOP_TITLE} description={WORKSHOP_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="page-shell">
			<header class="main-nav">
				<nav class="container nav-inner" aria-label="Primary">
					<a href="/" class="brand">austontatious.dev</a>
					<div class="nav-links">
						<a href="/#hero">Portfolio</a>
						<a href="/#projects">Projects</a>
						<a href="/workshops/" aria-current="page">Workshops</a>
					</div>
					<div class="nav-actions">
						<a href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">Email</a>
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/auston-horras-17022614/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
							LinkedIn
						</a>
					</div>
				</nav>
			</header>

			<main class="workshop-main">
				<section class="section workshop-hero">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<p class="eyebrow">Executive Workshop Offering</p>
						<h1>You Invested in AI. Is Your Team Seeing the Productivity Gains?</h1>
						<p class="lead workshop-lead">
							Most organizations now have access to powerful AI tools. The hard part is turning that
							access into consistent productivity across everyday work.
						</p>
						<p class="workshop-intro">
							This workshop helps teams learn how to actually work with modern AI systems, not just
							experiment with them.
						</p>
						<div class="workshop-hero-actions">
							<a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com?subject=AI%20Workshop%20Inquiry">
								Bring This Workshop to Your Team
							</a>
							<a class="button button-secondary" href="#workshop-formats">See Workshop Format</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Why AI Rollouts Are Struggling</h2>
							<p>
								Over the past year, many organizations have rolled out generative AI tools across their teams.
								Budgets have been approved. Expectations have been raised. Employees are experimenting with
								tools like ChatGPT, Copilot, and Gemini.
							</p>
							<p>
								And yet the results are often inconsistent. Some employees get remarkable results with AI.
								Others try it briefly and conclude it is unreliable or not very useful.
							</p>
							<p>
								Leadership is left asking a simple question: if we are investing in AI, why are we not seeing
								the productivity gains we expected?
							</p>
							<p>
								Across industries, the pattern is similar: tools are deployed quickly, expectations rise
								quickly, and real workflow changes happen slowly.
							</p>
							<p>
								Most organizations do not need another AI platform. They need their teams to actually know how
								to use the tools they already have.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Most AI Training Hasn’t Kept Up</h2>
							<p>
								The field has moved quickly, and much of the training available to teams has not kept pace
								with how modern AI systems actually behave.
							</p>
							<p>
								Many teams are still being taught prompt tricks or role-play prompting techniques that were
								more useful with early models than they are with modern systems.
							</p>
							<p>
								The missing skill is not memorizing magic prompts. The missing skill is learning how to
								structure work so AI can contribute reliably.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>The Gap Most Organizations Haven’t Solved Yet</h2>
							<p>
								Engineers building modern AI systems understand these tools differently than most
								knowledge workers expected to use them day to day.
							</p>
							<p>
								Internal technical teams often handle integration, security, and access, but normal teams are
								still left without a clear operating model for practical daily use.
							</p>
							<p>
								The missing piece is a translation layer that turns model behavior into repeatable work
								habits.
							</p>
							<p>This workshop exists to close that gap.</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>What This Workshop Actually Does</h2>
							<p>
								This workshop is not a software pitch, a product demo, or a trend talk. It is a practical
								session that helps teams understand how modern AI systems actually behave and how to work with
								them in ways that improve speed, quality, and consistency in real workflows.
							</p>
							<p>
								Teams learn how to structure prompts with scope, context, and constraints, how to use AI as a
								thinking partner instead of a search box, and how to evaluate where AI output is reliable
								versus risky.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner workshop-content">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>What Your Team Walks Away With</h2>
							<ul>
								<li>A shared framework for using AI effectively across roles</li>
								<li>Practical methods for scope, context, and constraint-driven prompting</li>
								<li>Better judgment about where AI is useful versus risky</li>
								<li>More consistent output quality across the team</li>
								<li>Workflows teams can apply immediately in writing, planning, analysis, and operational work</li>
							</ul>
						</article>

						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Why This Perspective Is Different</h2>
							<p>
								Many AI workshops are led by trend commentators or tool evangelists. This one is taught from
								the perspective of someone who actually builds AI systems and intelligent agents.
							</p>
							<p>
								The focus is translating implementation reality into practical team behavior, so what teams
								learn holds up under real constraints. RN experience is also relevant for healthcare and
								other regulated environments where reliability matters.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner workshop-content">
						<article class="workshop-panel" id="workshop-formats">
							<h2>Workshop Formats</h2>
							<ul>
								<li>60-minute executive briefings</li>
								<li>2-4 hour team workshops</li>
								<li>Customized sessions for technical, operational, or cross-functional teams</li>
								<li>Available remotely or on-site</li>
							</ul>
						</article>

						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Example Live Demonstrations</h2>
							<ul>
								<li>Showing how AI turns messy notes into structured reports</li>
								<li>Converting rough ideas into technical or operational specifications</li>
								<li>Comparing weak prompting habits with modern, constraint-driven workflows</li>
								<li>Using AI to critique, refine, and strengthen business documents</li>
								<li>Demonstrating how one AI system can help draft better instructions for another within governance constraints</li>
							</ul>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<div class="workshop-cta">
							<h2>Bring This Workshop to Your Team</h2>
							<p>
								If your organization has already invested in AI tools but is not yet seeing the productivity
								gains it expected, this workshop can help your teams learn how to use these systems
								effectively in real work.
							</p>
							<div class="cta-actions">
								<a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com?subject=AI%20Workshop%20Inquiry">
									Bring This Workshop to Your Team
								</a>
								<a class="button button-secondary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">
									Contact by Email
								</a>
								<a
									class="button button-secondary"
									href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/auston-horras-17022614/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noreferrer"
								>
									Connect on LinkedIn
								</a>
							</div>
							<a class="back-link workshop-back-link" href="/#hero">Back to portfolio</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>
			</main>

			<footer class="site-footer">
				<div class="container footer-inner">
					<p>Calm systems for clear outcomes.</p>
					<div class="footer-links">
						<a href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">Contact</a>
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/auston-horras-17022614/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
							LinkedIn
						</a>
						<a href="https://github.com/austontatious" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</footer>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
